# Git Quick Reference Guide

## 📋 Daily Workflow Commands

### Starting Work
```bash
# Switch to your team's main branch
git checkout backend/main

# Get latest changes
git pull origin backend/main

# Create new feature branch
git checkout -b backend/feature/my-feature-name
```

### During Work
```bash
# Check what files changed
git status

# Stage all changes
git add .

# Stage specific file
git add path/to/file.py

# Commit changes
git commit -m "feat: Description of changes"

# Push to GitHub
git push origin backend/feature/my-feature-name
```

### Finishing Work
```bash
# Push final changes
git push origin backend/feature/my-feature-name

# Go to GitHub and create Pull Request
# Base: backend/main
# Compare: backend/feature/my-feature-name
```

---

